            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">system：language transport</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">其他类</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">favor privilege mistake risk advantage benefit problem trouble surprise secret award prize diet property option case example sample score limit experience effort energy figure</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\"><span class=\"jiacu\">关于抽象名词的解读</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">总单词量：166个</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">类别：9个</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">因为抽象名词主要说的是“事”，而“事”都是“人”做的，所以，这个类别的词基本可以按照人“说的”“做的”“想的”来分类。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">除此之外，还有一些词因为并没有特别指明是哪件事，是一种泛指，在句子中扮演某一固定角色，所以就把它们归到了“其他类”。如mistake这个词，无法确定这个错误是指“说的话”还是“做的事”，只知道它会对事情产生消极的影响，所以就没法归类。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><h4 class=\"sigil_not_in_toc\">“二人传”“皮影戏”要咋说？</h4></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">抽象名词数量虽少，但分起类来可能要难得多，因为它们抽象嘛！不像人和东西，有鼻子有眼的一下子就能看出属于哪一类。但正因为抽象名词的分类更加复杂，所以意义也就更大。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">首先，跟具体名词一样，我们也可以用抽象名词所属的类别进行替代或释义。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">比如，concert（音乐会）这个词，因为它属于一种表演，所以就可以用它的类别词performance解释成下面这个样子：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">a public performance of music</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">那学会performance这个词对我们的口语表达有什么意义呢？咱们中国的地方戏太多了，什么黄梅戏、越剧、皮影戏，我们不可能记住它们每一个的英文名词，但我们学了performance这个词之后，下次带老外朋友去东北看“二人转”的时候就可以用这个词给他们介绍一下了：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">It is a local performance in North China. There're two players.They are singing and dancing to make people laugh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">这是中国北方的一种表演。有两个演员，他们又唱又跳逗观众开心。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">怎么样？说清楚了吧？有了这把尚方宝剑，你就可以很方便地跟老外侃中国的曲艺啦。布置个作业，试试怎么用performance来解释“皮影戏”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">比如，很多学校和公司都对学生或员工的穿着有要求，也就是我们通常所说的“着装规范”。“行为规范”这个词在英语中其实是有一个词code和它对应的。但是这个词并没有收录在我们的词表中，主要是因为这个词完全可以用词表中另外一个类别词进行解释，就是rule。所谓的“规范”不就是个规则吗？你可以说成：the rule of dressing或者dressing rule，如果连rule也不会表达那就说得更通俗一点，the way of wearing clothes。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">生活中有很多东西都是一种规矩，像什么法律啊，规章啊，制度啊等，甚至我们学英语要学的语法，也是一种规矩，只不过是指说话的规矩，都可以用rule来表达。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><h4 class=\"sigil_not_in_toc\">“服从政策”对不对？</h4></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">其次，有助于我们真正理解一些抽象词汇的含义，避免闹笑话。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">举例来说，policy这个词，我们之前学习的时候一般解释成“政策”，所以有的学习者就会有这样的表达obey the policy，意思是“服从政策”，因为我们的汉语中有这样约定俗成的表达。但大家从我们的R词汇表中可以看到，policy是属于plan这一类的，指的是某一机构或政党对一些重大事项的计划。既然是计划了，那么你可以“制定”（make），也可以“遵守”（follow），但不应该是“服从”（obey）。因为服从的对象要么是人，要么是法律、法规，而不是计划。所以，给抽象名词分类就可以避免我们犯搭配上的错误。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">比如knowledge这个词，我们一般把它理解为“知识”或者“文化”，所以有的学员会有he doesn't have knowledge（他没有文化）这种错误的说法。在我们的分类中，knowledge是归属到“信息”这一大类的，词典中的解释是：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">the information and skills you gain through education or experience</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">意思是“人们通过教育或经验所获取的信息或技能”等，既然是“信息或技能”，那每一个人都会有，只是多少的问题。所以，我们把这个词理解为“文化”是错误的，不能说He doesn't have knowledge.而我们说的“他没有文化”，其实是指“他没有上过学”或“没有受过好的教育”的意思，应该表达为He is not well educated.或者是He has never gone to school.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><h4 class=\"sigil_not_in_toc\">“婚礼”“葬礼”都一样</h4></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">最后，对抽象名词进行准确分类有助于我们提高对这个词的运用能力。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">同一类别的词除了可以用同一个词进行解释外，它们在使用上也有很多相通之处。举例来说，我们词表中有一个类别是occasion（场合），这个类别有以下几个词：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">meeting（会议）interview（面试）party（聚会）picnic（聚餐）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">wedding（婚礼）funeral（葬礼）barbecue（烧烤）ceremony（庆典）因为这些词指的都是某一个社交场合，所以它们都可以分别与下面的词搭配：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">首先是“有没有”的问题，所有的词都可用there be来表示。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">其次是“举办”的问题，多数可以与give, have或throw搭配，如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">Well have a wedding/ceremony/meeting.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">Well throw a party/picnic/barbecue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">Well give him a funeral/interview.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">还有“是否参加”的问题，都可以与go to搭配。如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">I will go to a meeting/interview/party/picnic/wedding/funeral.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">也可以与各种介词搭配，你可以说：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">I meet a beautiful girl at a wedding/party/picnic.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">也可以说：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">I brought you some food from the party/wedding/barbecue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">既然是一个社交场合，那就存在着是否有亮点的问题，所以你就可以说：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">The high point of the wedding is when they kissed each other.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">婚礼的高潮是他们互相亲吻。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">The only good of the ceremony is the food.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-1f83596b9618251c-a62746 twpub-1f83596b9618251c-9882b5\"><p class=\"bodycontent-text\">吃得还不错，是这次庆典的唯一亮点。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/1f83596b9618251c/text/000000794",
